--- log ---
2026-05-05T14:45Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

`tickets/tools/go/erg` (the project-local binary, built from the git-erg
submodule) currently requires a `Status:` header and rejects tickets without
it. The `ticket-new` skill instructs agents to omit `Status:` — "Note:
no `Status:` header — `erg validate` rejects it."

This inconsistency means every `ticket-new` run either (a) fails validation
until `Status:` is manually added, or (b) silently violates the skill
spec. Both happened in the 2026-05-05 session (tickets 0087, 0088).

The source of truth is `tickets/FORMAT.md`, which lists `Status` as required.
The ticket-new skill is wrong, OR the binary was rebuilt from a newer spec
that dropped `Status:`. Either way, the binary and the skill must agree.

## Actions

1. Check the git-erg submodule HEAD and read the current validator source
   to determine which behaviour is authoritative (Status required vs. omitted).
2. If the submodule binary is stale: `cd tickets/tools && go build -o go/erg .`
   and commit the new binary.
3. If the skill is wrong: update `skills/ticket-new/SKILL.md` to restore the
   `Status: open` line in the template.
4. Verify: `erg validate tickets/0088-beat-outcome-instrumentation.erg` passes
   without adding or removing `Status:`.

## Exit criteria

- `erg validate` and `ticket-new` agree on whether `Status:` is required.
- All open tickets in `tickets/` pass validation without manual edits.
